<http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.sajb.2020.08.029>
    dc:creator "Elliott, T. L.", "Muasya, A. M." ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "A taxonomic revision of the Epischoenus group of Schoenus (Cyperaceae, tribe Schoeneae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "316" ;
    bibo:journal "South African Journal of Botany" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-12-31" ;
    bibo:startPage "296" ;
    bibo:volume "135" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496814>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496820>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496824>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496826>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496844> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496814>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Examples of plants from six species of the Epischoenus group found in southern Africa, showing the corresponding inflorescences beneath each plant: A and G—S.crinitus; B and H—S. adnatus; C and I—S. gracillimus; D and J—S. schonlandii; E and K—S. lucidus; and F and L—S. neovillosus. The black scale bar adjacent to the inflorescence in L represents 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496814/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496820>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Examples of spikelets from 11 species of the Epischoenus group found in southern Africa: A—S.dregeanus; B—S.complanatus; C—S. quadrangularis; D—S. selinae; E—S.rigidus; F—S.crinitus; G—S.adnatus; H—S.gracillimus; I—S.schonlandii; J—S.lucidus; and K—S.neovillosus. The black scale bar beside K represents 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496820/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496824>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Spikelet of S.adnatus (A) showing the spikelet receptacle adnate to the proximal glume contrasted with the spikelet of S.crinitus (B), which shows the typical position of the spikelet receptacle relative to the proximal glume in species in this group." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496824/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496826>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Examples of nutlets from 11 species of the Epischoenus group found in southern Africa: A—S. dregeanus; B—S.complanatus; C—S. quadrangularis; D—S. selinae; E—S.rigidus; F—S.crinitus; G—S.adnatus; H—S.gracillimus; I—S.schonlandii; J—S.lucidus; and K—S.neovillosus. The black scale bar beside K represents 1 mm. Fully formed, mature nutlets of S.crinitus and S. neovillosus have yet to be observed." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496826/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496844>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Documented locations of S.adnatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496844/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

